By Ma Suping, special correspondent, southern weekend

Editor in chief | Cao Haidong

Just after the Lunar Year of the rat, the Zhang family entered the era of "planned economy" .

A family of five, four dishes a day soup, "plan to eat. ". Pork is too expensive, reserve meat taste is not so fresh, the family can only eat a long period of Bacon, preserved fish, "are prepared years ago. ".

On the 12th month, the city of Wuhan was sealed off. twenty-nine. Zhang Xu, who lives in the bubuting garden community in Jiang'an District, knows how difficult life can be: Because private cars are not registered with the traffic control bureau, they can not go on the road, and their daily life, such as shopping, is greatly affected.

Early in the morning of February 11, Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and control again upgraded: The city's residential communities to start closed management, to minimize the flow of personnel. Each family with a pass, every three days can be assigned to go out to purchase living materials.

The Zhangs had to turn their attention to food and vegetables. The leafy Greens from the Baibu Pavilion store in Zhongbai Warehouse had just arrived. Zhang Xu, whose monthly basic salary was only 1,500 yuan, bought nearly 300 yuan of vegetables, meat and rice in one breath. Want to buy flour but have not found, a ask only to know that flour is now particularly popular, 10 am supermarket opened not long before sold out.

Behind A hundred-word notice is the daily life of a city of more than 10 million people.

For Zhang Xu, a 40-year-old, there was a different "smell" in the Xinhua report as early as the morning of February 6. "The state of war must not be used as a deserter, or it will be forever impaled on the stigma of history, " said Sun Chunlan, a vice premier whose wartime speech was thrust into the hands of more than ten million citizens through various news channels.

"State of war" highlights the severity of the epidemic. Since February 2, the number of newly confirmed cases of coronary pneumonia in Wuhan has broken 1,000 per day. THREE LINES OF EPIDEMIC PREVENTION HAVE BEEN URGENTLY ESTABLISHED: Community and fever outpatient clinics will form the first line of Defense, and fever patients will be thoroughly screened from the grass-roots level; and shelter hospitals will form the second line of Defense, focus on patients with mild illness; fixed-point Hospital and Fire Mountain, Thunder Mountain Hospital constitute the Third Line of Defense, rescue critically ill, critically ill patients.

In 25 days, from New Year's Eve on January 24 to February 17,208 medical teams and 25,972 personnel flew to Wuhan. Twelve shelter hospitals were launched, providing 20,461 beds; 45 designated hospitals opened 19,161 beds; and 16 provincial universities were requisitioned as reserve isolation points, with 15,000 isolation rooms available. This is a country's emergency response to an outbreak.

The contradiction of "medical run-out" has been initially solved with the investment of huge medical resources and the reconstruction of grading diagnosis and treatment system.

Based on this, Chinese Academy of Engineering Academician Zhong Nanshan said bluntly, "Wuhan has not yet completely blocked the transmission of human to human" . On February 12, Chen Yixin, deputy head of the Central Guidance Group and Secretary General of the Central Political and Legal Affairs Commission, called for "three-volume control" : Control of increments, reduction of stocks and prevention of variables.

"closed city" on the 24th, Wuhan launched a 3-day centralized network-style investigation. On Feb. 16, Wang Zhonglin, the party secretary of Wuhan and a member of the Standing Committee of the Hubei Provincial Party Committee, who has only been in office for four days, demanded in a video conference that "no one should be left behind, no one should be left behind. ". He said, "only to find people, to find people, to implement the 'receivable collection. " '.

"Wuhan is the place of decisive battle. We should concentrate our efforts on the war of annihilation, not on the protracted war of slackness and slackness. " Wang Zhonglin made a "pre-war mobilization" to the city's cadres.

1
Desperate Times

1

###Desperate Times

To be precise, the "great Armageddon" in Wuhan began on February 5.

On the same day, Wuhan New Pneumonia Epidemic Prevention and Control Command issued a "death order" : no later than February 7 to find out all suspected cases, February 5 at 24 pm, to treat all confirmed patients.

At that time, Wuhan, the epidemic is in an outbreak of epidemic, in order to show the degree of infection in color map of the national epidemic, the color of Wuhan to black. Many people who can not get help in time have no choice but to use social media platforms to seek help, exposing their full privacy to millions of Internet users -- down to their home address and identity card number -- as a standard help thread format.

Liu Li, a 77-year-old retired teacher, finally opened his Weibo account at 1:00 am after some trial and error, just begging for a chance to save his granddaughter's life. Her daughter died before being diagnosed, and the couple, both in their 70s, and their 13-year-old granddaughter, were infected. The first message on his Weibo page was just two words, "hello. ".

In Wuhan during the extraordinary period, although the quota of nucleic acid testing has increased, the speed of renovation and new hospital construction can not catch up with the daily number of more than 1,000 newly diagnosed cases, and still many people can not be hospitalized.

From January 27, the third day of the Lunar New Year to February 14, less than 20 days, Hubei Film Studio Employees Chang Kai and his family of four died. In the suicide note, Chang Kai wrote when his father had an attack, "sent to many hospitals for treatment, have no beds to receive, multiple help, but also a bed hard to get, extremely disappointed, go home to save themselves. ". A few days of filial piety before bed, the virus also swallowed him and his sister's body.

At that time, Wuhan, centralized treatment of critically ill patients with gold and silver pool, lung, central south of these three designated hospitals, only 110 critical beds. The Vulcan and Raytheon hospitals also have only 30 intensive care beds. Because a bed is hard to find, an ambulance sent a patient to six hospitals were not received, finally had to send him home.

On Feb. 8, the day her mother was dying, Euna Lee, a Hanyang woman in Pajamas, sounded a gong on her balcony for help. EUNA Lee, who had worked in the health care system, knew a number of doctor friends, but called everyone he knew and was told the beds were too tight. The community's response was the same, "registered to the street, in line. ".

In practice, Wuhan new pneumonia epidemic prevention and control headquarters February 5, the "death order" did not meet expectations. On February 8, Jiang Chaoliang, then the Communist Party secretary of Hubei Province, in Wuhan, where he oversaw the epidemic's prevention and control, reiterated the need to test all suspected patients in the city within two days.

A day later, Wuhan launched the "collection should be" investigation. In fact, as early as January 24, the main leaders of Hubei Province and Wuhan attended a meeting that mentioned "ensuring the unconditional admission of all suspected patients" . The next day, the Wuhan Command meeting made it clear that "the immediate implementation of the district has not admitted patients beds, priorities, to ensure that 'should receive all. " '.

Starting on February 9,34,000 civil servants and employees of state-owned enterprises sank into 1,107 communities in the three towns of Wuhan, covering 24 hours a day the screening of "four categories of people" (confirmed, suspected, feverish and close contacts) , ensure that every confirmed, suspected, Febrile and close contact person is accommodated in the then 31 designated hospitals, 3 shelter hospitals and over 100 centralized isolation observation points converted from hotels, schools, etc. .

If we can pull this off, the most dangerous source of infection in Wuhan could be completely shut down.

2
"Who are you? Where are you from? Where are you going? "

2

###"Who are you? Where are you from? Where are you going? "

Received a street "zero" urge call, is February 9 in the morning. Cheung Kuen, a community officer in Jianghan District, Wuhan, faces more than 5,000 households and nearly 20,000 residents.

To date, more than 20 people in the community have been confirmed as infected with NCP. Although want to through the network as far as possible to achieve "no contact investigation" , but many parents-in-law use the elderly machine, will not go online, the phone also can not get through, had to house investigation. "We have a rule that when you knock on the door, you have to stay 1.5 meters away from the door, or people will fear you have the virus, " Zhang said.

Zhang's desk, in the deepest part of the community service station, is filled with registration forms, documenting the work done by community workers since the end of January. For the community, the real "state of war" began on Feb. 9, when a staff member registered a form for residents under the heading "state of war access records. ".

On that day, Zhang Juan and four staff members were sitting at a community service station before 9 a.m. , making repeated phone calls, asking residents to report their temperature and health status. After dropping off the phone, they drew a check in the last line of the record book to complete a house search. At the end of the day, each person made at least 150 phone calls, "the phone is hot. ". Fortunately, there was no report of a new fever that day. For Zhang Juan, who has been busy since years ago, this is undoubtedly a great comfort.

On the afternoon of February 9, Zhang Juan received a phone call from the leadership, the day must have not completed the two nucleic acid testing of suspected personnel have been lined up. Before this, nucleic acid examination wants to wait 3 days to be able to give a result, apparent now speed up, can give a result the next day after sending an examination. Between 8:00 p.m. and 9:00 p.m. , she answered and dialed nearly 20 times. Some seek counseling, some seek bed help, and some cry that they are sick and seek psychological comfort.

In the eyes of residents, the community seems to be a lifesaver, once the requirements are not met, complaints come. Reports of disease, difficult home, fill out the form, contact the driver assigned to the community to pick up patients... The community has a dozen staff, years ago someone resigned under pressure.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Personal disinfection by the community screening officer. (Xinhua News Agency / Photo)

Zhang Juan and her colleagues have too many "moments of wanting to collapse. ". A man in his 80s had a fever, and his son came in demanding a solution. "We told him to wait for a bed, and he scolded me for being a secretary, " he said. "Do you think this is a decision that a community can make? "

February 11, the implementation of Wuhan District Closure Order, the community has a lot of heavy burden. Community workers, sinking cadres of Party members, community security guards shift to work, every day hand-held temperature gun, asked countless philosophical questions: Who are you? Where did you come from? Where are we going?

Hongshan District Huada home known as the "most cattle district" , 1,766 households only one person infected. If someone in the neighborhood gets into trouble, you can find out everything you can about him. Due to the outbreak during the closure of the community, Wuhan Caidian Street a pyramid selling group ran out of food surrendered, only to the community for help.

Baibu Pavilion Garden Community in front of the Baibu yating community, a little girl can not move the courier box, security wanted to help up, was refused. The security guard didn't blame her. Times are tough.

As tough as they may seem, fear is also haunting the people of Wuhan. The mortician carries the deceased from the side by that moment, Zhang Juan subconsciously identified the wind direction, for fear of the virus with the wind to attach themselves.

3
Dismissal, change of command, high-pressure supervision

3

###Dismissal, change of command, high-pressure supervision

The key to the war against "epidemic disease" is to find out the exact number and to divide up the "four categories of personnel" .

The "due diligence" survey, launched on Feb. 9, was not as effective as it was supposed to be. Officials later said that "the percentage of households surveyed reached 98.6 percent and the percentage of people surveyed reached 99 percent. ".

Wang Zhonglin, standing committee member of the Hubei Provincial Party Committee and Secretary of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee, said at the video dispatch meeting of the NCP epidemic prevention and Control Headquarters that, before this big investigation "big and turn into more" "in the implementation of the investigation on the attitude is not resolute, measures are not strict, Mesh too big" .

On the evening of February 9, during the transfer of newly hospitalized patients with severe pneumonia to the sino-french Xincheng district of Wuhan Tongji Hospital, not only were the transport vehicles in poor conditions in Wuchang District due to the lagging work, disorganization and disorganization, street and community workers also do not provide car-following services, causing critically ill patients to wait for long periods of time and then lose control of their emotions.

Through the media exposure of this strong approach, the problem has been extraordinary speed and processing power.

"Why don't the Party cadres who are responsible for transporting critically ill patients follow the train? Wuhan is now in a state of war, and these people are behaving very badly. " Three people, including the deputy mayor of Wuhan, were urgently interviewed by the Central Committee's Hubei Guidance Group, demanding an apology to the patients one by one and serious accountability to those responsible.

At that time, in Wuhan alone, the number of deaths from NCP was close to the global death toll from SARS in 2003. "People's Daily" commented that the interview is to release a strong signal: The war "epidemic" current, dereliction of duty, will be severely accountable.

On February 8, the central government sent two men to Hubei from the air  --. On the same day, the Party secretary and director of the Hubei Provincial Health Commission were both removed from their posts, with Wang Hesheng holding both positions.

Two days later, President Xi Jinping, wearing a mask and stretching his wrist to take his temperature, was in Beijing researching the prevention and control of the new pneumonia outbreak. "In times of emergency, we don't shake hands, " he told residents. After surveying the community, Xi connected via video link to the Jinyintan Hospital, the Wuhan Union Hospital Hospital and the Huoshenshan hospital at Temple of Earth Hospital, where he addressed Wuhan, saying, "If Wuhan Wins, Hubei Wins, and if Hubei wins, the whole country wins. ".

February 13, the war "epidemic" is in full swing, Hubei Provincial Party Committee personnel adjustment. Ying Yong, the mayor of Shanghai, took over from Jiang Chaoliang, who was born into the financial system, as party chief of Hubei Province. Wang Zhonglin, a member of Shandong's Standing Committee and Party Secretary of Jinan, replaced Ma Guoqiang, who was born into a business family, as party chief of Hubei and Wuhan. This fire line changes a commander in chief, let a lot of people think of during SARS period turn the situation Beijing temporarily changes a commander in chief.

Zhang Juan, who is busy checking her community and filling out forms, has no time for local officials to "get out of class" or watch the news broadcast, but she can feel the pressure spreading in layers: every morning, middle and evening, she receives calls from the street, the other side kept asking to confirm the case of the arrangement to what stage.

The pressure has reached its peak in the last three days of sweeping the city's Internet: Wang Zhonglin, the secretary of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee, oversaw the battle during a video conference held by the city's Xinguan pneumonia epidemic prevention and control headquarters: Another confirmed or suspected case has been found at home, "Take District Party secretary, district chief is asked. ".

"The dead order given by the leaders to the community is to give priority to ensuring that 100 percent of the confirmed patients are admitted, and once the supervision team finds that someone has confiscated it, they will be held accountable, " Zhang said, adding that the new secretary had made an effort.

4
"Slow increment" of Shelter Hospital

4

###"Slow increment" of Shelter Hospital

In Wuhan's "three lines of defense" , the Shelter Hospital isolates the patients with mild illness from the outside world to prevent the spread of the virus to other people, playing a "slow incremental" role. Although the hardware conditions are not comparable to the fixed-point hospital, but it is the best choice for patients with mild illness.

Wuhan is not the first time a shelter hospital has been seen, as it was during the Wenchuan County and Yushu earthquakes. The idea of building a shelter hospital was not put forward by Wuhan, but was proposed by experts and pushed by the central government.

On February 1, Chinese Academy of Engineering, a respiratory and critical care specialist, arrived in Wuhan. Wang Chen, who was the head of a medical team in Beijing during the SARS era, thought it was a bad idea to set up a shelter hospital after seeing a large number of patients floating in society, living in isolation at home and being prone to cross infection.

Kong Hon's Shelter Hospital, which was built within 48 hours of the national emergency medical team's arrival in Wuhan on February 4, is still in a state of constant sorting out. Nearly 2,000 beds were taken over by medical teams from different provinces. In order to better understand patients'conditions, the team, which was drawn up by the second people's Hospital of Guangdong Province, proposed to the headquarters that each medical team should be stationed in a fixed area every day.

"Crash" shelter hospital, medical care and service facilities inevitably can not keep up. In Wuhan in early February, the temperature at 1:00 a.m. was often just 3 degrees, and there was no heating in the Shelter Hospital transformed by the Convention and Exhibition Center. Some elderly people couldn't eat well or sleep well, causing little tantrums in front of the medical staff.

Late on the night of February 7, Hu Minghong, a native of Hankou, waited for four hours in the open air outside his Wembley Arena in the rain before being admitted to Wuchang's shelter hospital. Luckily, things were on track -- everyone in Florida was fitted with an electric blanket, and on Lantern Festival, he had roasted pork with radish and shrimp with Gei Wai.

On Feb. 15, when Ying Yong, the party secretary of Hubei Province, arrived at the Living Room Shelter Hospital in Wuhan after just three days in office, his first concern was "what's the temperature in the cabin now? "

At the Shelter Hospital, a doctor is responsible for about 50 patients. For similar treatment, Hu Minghong was prescribed abidol hydrochloride, Oseltamivir phosphate, Lianhua Qingwen capsule and the traditional Chinese medicine pneumonia No. 1 prescription "cold dampness and stagnation of the lung decoction" . The nurse will remind him to take his medicine, but the patients are too busy to take care of themselves, so the patients need to remind each other.

Jun Wang, deputy chief of the medical team at the Hubei Provincial Cancer Hospital, was one of the first doctors to be admitted to Wuchang's shelter hospital. He and his team developed a "patient autonomy" management model -- A patient-divided, district-elected, patient-controlled order. The district chief of area a wrote a long article about the Disease Center and Shared It on wechat groups; the district chief of Area B found that the stadium lights could not be turned off at night when he went to bed, so he contacted friends and sent over 200 eye masks.

The turnover of beds in the shelter hospital is also accelerating. On February 11, the first 28 patients were discharged from Wuchang's shelter hospital. Since then, more than 250 patients with mild illness have been discharged from four shelter hospitals, and new patients have been transferred here. At the same time, there are also eight shelter hospital opened, is expected to treat more than 20,000 patients.

At the time of illness, people are often moved by ordinary things. A photo of a masked "bookworm" half-asleep reading a book has been trending on Weibo, with even the author's Francis Fukuyama retweeting the news.

Xinjiang Bahar, a doctor at the People's Hospital, dressed in protective clothing, danced a black horse dance with his patients. Medical staff from Qilu Hospital in Shandong Province have compiled a practical manual for Wuhan dialect in 48 hours. It is called "ziyi-ha: Wipe" , "you are quite awake: You are very beautiful" , reducing communication barriers with the elderly. "It's very simple, " explained a paramedic who wrote "black duck week" and "hot and dry noodles" on his suit.

5
"Top match" resources are out in force

5

###"Top match" resources are out in force

In Wuhan, where medical resources are in short supply, designated hospitals focus on rescuing critical cases and taking on the role of "stock reduction" .

Having a bed in this modern metropolis means having professional medical staff and equipment to support you. But on the most intense day, only 123 beds remained in the city's designated hospitals. "It's better to have a bed waiting than a bed waiting, " Sun Chunlan said on Feb. 11 during an inspection tour of the shelter hospital, adding more beds and capacity.

It's a race to the death. During the construction peak period, 7,435 construction workers and 1,491 excavators and cranes were working around the clock at the Leishenshan Hospital. On January 24, February 2, February 13, February 17, the People's Air Force four times to fly to Wuhan, the Air Force transport aircraft 30 times, emergency transport troops to support Hubei medical teams and supplies. On Feb. 9, more than 40 chartered planes flew nearly 6,000 medical personnel to Wuhan Tianhe Airport. North Concord, South Xiangya, East Qilu, West Hwaseo, the medical sector, the four "Heaven Group" to join Wuhan.

Six hospitals, including the Beijing Hospital, the Peking Union Medical College Hospital and the China Japan Hospital, were also involved in the battle. Even some fourth-and fifth-tier cities, such as Guyuan in Ningxia and Huangyuan County in Xining, have drawn their best troops to assist Wuhan.

More pressing than the usual beds are the intensive care units and supporting resources. In Tongji Hospital, the Central Court district, the Guanggu Hospital district, the Western Hospital of Xiehe Hospital, the Eastern Hospital of Hubei Provincial People's Hospital... . Hospitals under the jurisdiction of the CPC Committee and provincial hospitals in Han were urgently transformed into designated hospitals for the centralized treatment of severe cases, the number of beds expanded to 5,000.

The "top allocation" resources of the national medical field are mobilized to take over these hospitals or wards in an organized way. On Feb. 1, a team led by Zhang Naofu, deputy director of the Guangzhou Medical University, took over the intensive-care unit. At least 10 percent of the hospital's 800 patients were critically ill and needed to be intubated, compared with 20 beds in the ICU. Ma Xiaowei, director of the National Health Commission, and Jiao Yahui, deputy director of the Medical Administration and Hospital Authority, were also anxious and asked what measures could be taken to reduce the case fatality rate.

"Invasive Catheterization in the general ward is the only way, " Zhang replied. After coming to Wuhan, Zhang was an expert and a housekeeper, not only in charge of clinical work, but also in charge of logistics, even using personal connections to borrow equipment from everywhere.

The National Health Commission leaders on the spot, do everything possible to deploy equipment. More than 2,000 ICU nurses from all over the country have been transferred to Wuhan. The State Health Commission also requires the medical teams to bring their own breathing machines, monitors, ECMO and other supporting life support equipment.

The health care workers with the patients are also breaking through the barrier themselves. Heavy protective clothing is wearing a 6 hours, which means no water can not go to the toilet, the first experience of "three-level protection" 90 nurses cycle dizzy, chest tightness, retching state, can only squat on the ground for temporary relief. Doctors have found that a low bridge of the nose is also a good thing, at least the N95 mask will not wear the nose pressure sore.

At a news conference on the evening of February 10, Ma Guoqiang, then secretary of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee, said that after two days of efforts to open up beds, all of the 1,499 critically ill patients who had not been hospitalized before had been admitted.

Not all war stories have happy endings. The Didi Express driver, Lin Fang, received a call from a nurse at Wuhan's Central Hospital, who failed to resuscitate a critically ill patient that night. Lin Fang asked her if she was afraid, she said of course. The two men then fell silent, not knowing what to say.

6
When will the inflection point occur?

6

###When will the inflection point occur?

On February 12,538 patients were discharged from hospitals in Wuhan, with the number of new confirmed cases dropping for the second day in a row.

On this day, the Shanghai Aid Hubei Medical Team leader Zheng Junhua began the 20th day of work in the Jintan Hospital. As the first medical team to arrive in Wuhan, through the initial adaptation and running-in, his mood has long been calm, only hope that the Wuhan epidemic inflection point can appear as soon as possible, "for the medical team, this means hope and confidence. ".

However, on February 13, the Hubei Provincial Health and Health Commission, in an unusual move, postponed the daily release of the epidemic around 7:00. At 8:30, "Wuhan Release" official micro-push the latest epidemic data, Zhang Juan stopped work, stunned the city of Florida Florida, 13,436 newly confirmed cases (including clinical cases) , nearly 10 times more than in the past every day.

In fact, one day ago on February 12, at a meeting of the Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters, Chen Yixin pointed out that the severe situation of the epidemic in Wuhan was still in an outbreak stage, with new cases still at a high level, the number of infected people is not yet fully known, and there is no more accurate estimate of the spread of the forecast.

The good news is that the change in statistical caliber has finally allowed those patients who have been delayed for many days to be admitted to the hospital with a clinical diagnosis that matches the CT findings. The number of new cases in Wuhan has dropped sharply since the start of the 13th, but the city remains the most affected in the country.

When Academician Zhong Nanshan's team held a teleconference with the ICU treatment team of the Guangdong medical team in front of Wuhan on Feb. 17, Zhong Nanshan pointed out that the rate of building or renovating hospitals is far less than the growth rate of more than 1,000 confirmed cases per day, it is not realistic to reduce the mortality rate without cutting off the source of transmission.

Among the confirmed cases in Wuhan, 18% were seriously ill. Since taking over the ICU, the Zhong Nanshan team has admitted 36 critically ill patients, with a nearly 50 percent mortality rate, often leaving the head of the Zhong Nanshan team in Han flummoxed.

The average length of stay in Wuhan from onset to hospitalization was 9.84 days for severe cases, according to Jiao Yahui, deputy director of the medical and Health Bureau of the NHFPC. During the 10-day waiting period, the mild illness became severe, causing the critically ill patients in Wuhan to be sicker than in other areas and more difficult to treat than during SARS. The illness drags on and on, and when it reaches the end of its life and is transferred to the ICU, the doctor is often powerless to help.

"The incoming patients are too late. " Most of the 16-bed intensive care unit patients have been referred from other hospitals and some have experienced cardiac arrest. With no specific treatment for the disease worldwide, Peng Zhiyong, director of the Department of Critical Care Medicine at the Central South University, and his team are trying to ensure that patients do not die from lack of oxygen.

7
General Attack "clear zero"

7

###General Attack "clear zero"

In the investment of huge human and material resources, Wuhan is still not thoroughly check the number of infection, there are still patients can not reach the isolation point, can not get medical care. This armageddon seems to have no sign of ending.

On February 16, Wuhan launched a three-day intensive grid search to find out how much. On This Day, Wuhan issued four orders to upgrade the prevention and control standards. Wang Zhonglin particularly stressed the implementation of five "100 percent" : 100 percent for confirmed patients, 100 percent for suspected patients, 100 percent for fever patients, and 100 percent for close contacts, 100% of the residential area is under 24-hour closed management.

On This Day, the Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters set up a new bed support group, Disease Control Group, the Party Building Assessment Group, the Chinese medical team reception and Coordination Group. Compared with the establishment of the command, these teams are all focused on the current epidemic prevention work focus, difficulties, weaknesses, weaknesses.

On the evening of the 16th, after receiving the notice of big clearance, the Golden City of Vanke on Zhangjiawan Street in Hongshan District began to prepare. Xu Qiusi, the deputy secretary of the community, went into the residential building, opened the electric meter box and checked against the check-in form. There are grid staff to go door-to-door building residents light up the situation, compared with the previous survey data.

14 cadres were promoted in the line of fire. Chen Yixin said that in the line of fire to select the battle, Mengjiang, really put the "official hat" to inspire more party members and cadres in the battle of Remember the Titans, hard work and dedication.

The atmosphere of the final battle continues. Peking Union Medical College Hospital transformed the Tumor Center into a new hospital for the treatment of critically ill patients with coronary pneumonia, adding 850 beds. Doctors continue to pour into Wuhan, and some hospitals have nearly emptied their staffs of respiratory, infectious and ICU departments.

In order to prevent people from not reporting their fevers and taking medicines in private, Hubei Province thoroughly screened people who ordered fever-reducing and cough-relieving drugs through physical pharmacies or online, and even convenience stores were equipped with temperature examiners.

From February 18, all supermarkets in Wuchang District will only accept community group purchase customers. They will no longer sell daily necessities to individuals. If they violate the regulations, they will be punished according to the relevant requirements of the "wartime state"  In Hanyang District, shoppers entering a supermarket are required to hold a "resident pass" issued by the office of the new Hanyang District pneumonia prevention and control headquarters.

On February 17, no new cases were reported in the Shennongjia, and all the confirmed cases were cured. A "clean slate" has been achieved, which gives confidence to Wuhan, which is in the "most arduous and critical phase" of the epidemic prevention and control, as Chen Yixin said: "want to epidemic situation out of the 'inflection point' , first to confidence out of the 'inflection point' . ".

Wuhan "Armageddon" , only Wuhan themselves know how big the wound, they come from the downstairs ambulance or funeral car, close friends for help. Outside the whirlpool people can only see a number, can not see behind the joys and sorrows.

Underneath the rubble, there's hope. As if pressed the pause button, the Vortex Center of Wuhan is unusually cold and cheerless. Only at night, light show wall letters flashing "Wuhan refueling. ".

(at the request of the interviewee, Zhang Xu, Zhang Juan and Lin Fang were given pseudonyms. Southern weekend reporter Wang Weikai contributed to this report.)
